        "story_eyebrow": "THE VAMAS STORY",
        "story_heading": "<p>Where sarees<br><em>get obsessed.</em></p>",
        "story_body": "<p>It started in Mumbai in the 1960s, a time when sarees swirled like magic carpets. Vamas began not just as a brand, but as a mission to elevate the saree — crafting blouses that turn it into a masterpiece. Five decades on, Vamas is a family tradition, and our love for quality, craftsmanship, and understanding what makes a woman feel special hasn't changed.</p><p>A saree deserves a partner in crime, not just any old blouse. Our blouses are a symphony of fabrics — the silky whisper of silk, the rich drape of brocade, the comfy coolness of cotton, the modern edge of velvet — meticulously crafted by artisans who pour their heritage into every stitch.</p><p>We're all about tradition with a modern twist: classic silhouettes like halter necks and sweetheart necklines reimagined for today, alongside new-age styles like peplums, off-the-shoulder cuts, and capes — so you find the perfect match for your saree, family heirloom or brand new.</p>",
